21 September 2020 Following the address by the President, his Excellency President Cyril Ramaphosa on Wednesday, 16 September 2020, on the progress in the national effort to contain the Covid-19 pandemic; Police Minister,  General Bheki Cele and the SAPS management will on Tuesday 22 September 2020, brief the media on law enforcement during the National Lockdown Alert Level One. In addition to this, Minister Cele will provide futher details on the Gender based Violence  (GBV)hotspot areas. Details of the briefing are as follows:Date:   Tuesday, 22 September 2020Time:  14:30 for 15h00 Media Participation: Journalists may view the briefing via live streaming on the SA Government Facebook page, Twitter and YouTube channels on the links below. Facebook: http://facebook.com/GovernmentZA(link is external) (link is external) Twitter: http://twitter.com/GovernmentZA(link is external) (link is external) YouTube: http://youtube.com/GovernmentZA(link is external)(link is external) SABC will provide pool feed as follows: Satellite         Amos7 @ 4 WestDownlink       12649.5 Mhz VSymbol Rate 2.7 MSym/sModulation    8PSKVideo            HD H.264 @ 4.2.0 Enquiries:Mr William BaloyiCell: 083 390 7147 Issued by: Government Communication and Information System (GCIS)